Another key trend shaping the automotive differential market is the emphasis on autonomous driving capabilities and advanced driver-assistance systems (ADAS). These technologies rely on precision-engineered differentials to ensure smooth power transfer and coordination between wheels for enhanced performance and safety. Market players are investing in research and development to incorporate smart differential solutions that can seamlessly integrate with autonomous vehicle platforms. Moreover, the increasing consumer preference for off-road adventures and recreational activities is driving the demand for robust differentials that can withstand harsh terrains and provide superior traction in challenging environments.

